title: Heritage Elegance with Development Opportunities!!
description:
We are proud to present Bronte Homestead, Circa 1886, a stunningly preserved Victorian-era residence nestled on an expansive 1,992sqm (approx.) allotment in the heart of Burwood, one of Melbourne's prized eastern suburbs.

Rich in history and character, this unique family home offers timeless charm along with exciting future development potential (S.T.C.A.), a rare opportunity in Melbourne's sought-after eastern corridor that's been in the making for over 139 years.

The Homestead - Timeless Character with Modern Comforts

• A rare single-level, double-brick residence that effortlessly blends period charm with spacious, functional living. Set beneath soaring ceilings, the home features four generous bedrooms and three well-appointed bathrooms.

• Sun-drenched living zones overlook approximately 800sqm of beautifully landscaped, north-facing gardens, while a wide colonial-style bluestone verandah wraps around the home, perfect for relaxing afternoons or stylish entertaining.

• Rich in original detail, the interiors showcase polished Baltic pine floors, exposed brick alcoves, ceiling roses, and ornate cornices. A vast formal lounge, cosy breakfast room with potbelly stove heater, and a light-filled modern farmhouse kitchen (with skylight, 5-burner gas cooktop, and garden access) complete the living experience.

• The flexible rear layout offers scope for future renovation or expansion, supported by a range of comforts including hydronic heating, split-system air conditioning, gas log fireplace, dual hot water systems (gas & electric), solar electricity, and 18,000L of rainwater storage.

• A standalone double-brick garage with natural light, remote roller door, and built-in shelving adds the finishing touch to this unique, heritage-rich property.

The Garden - A Lush and Productive Sanctuary

• Step into a serene, north-facing haven where beauty meets bounty. Designed for low-maintenance living, the garden features a blend of native and edible landscaping that thrives year-round.

• Admire the award-praised "Bronte Heritage" Cabernet Franc and Muscat vines, alongside a rich variety of homegrown produce citrus, stone fruits, apples, pears, kiwifruit, and heritage selections.

• Five raised vegetable beds, compost bins, a tool shed, and gravity-fed irrigation ensure sustainable, hands-on gardening.

• Children will love the cubby house, swing set, and expansive lawn areas, all shaded by mature trees including oak, wild strawberry, eucalypts, and lilly pilly.

Prime Location - Coveted Eastern Suburb & Distinctive Setting

• A hidden gem nestled in a tranquil, tree - lined pocket of Melbourne's eastern suburbs.

• Enjoy the convenience of walking to Deakin University and being just moments from some of the area's most prestigious primary and secondary schools, including PLC, Huntingtower School, and Kingswood College.

• The upcoming Suburban Rail Loop station adds exceptional future connectivity, while you're just minutes from the acclaimed Burwood Brickworks, Box Hill's renowned dining precinct, and major transport links.

• Privately set well back from the street, the home features a sweeping horseshoe driveway with secure parking for up to eight vehicles.

Endless Potential - Heritage Charm Meets Modern Opportunity

Whether you're planning your dream home or considering a savvy investment, this exceptional property delivers remarkable flexibility: Restore, extend, and elevate the heritage-listed residence, making the most of the expansive block and prized north-facing aspect; Explore commercial possibilities with professional consulting rooms or business premises (STCA), while retaining space to build a separate dwelling at the rear; Unlock development potential with a strategic subdivision (STCA), creating two brand-new homes and maximising land value.

More Than a Home - A Rare Urban Sanctuary

Bronte Homestead is not just a residence, it's an extraordinary retreat in one of Melbourne's most tightly held enclaves. Whether you're a growing family in search of space, a developer securing a blue-chip landholding, or a heritage lover drawn to timeless elegance, this exceptional property offers a unique fusion of character, scale, and opportunity just 15km from Melbourne's CBD.

Opportunities like Bronte Homestead are incredibly rare and tightly held, this is your chance to secure something truly special. To arrange a private inspection or request further details, contact Florence Law on 0431 178 880 or Robert Fidanza on 0432 820 277 today, don't wait and risk missing out on what could be a once in a lifetime opportunity.

Centrally located, the stylish kitchen has gorgeous timber flooring, premium appliances, twin pantries, glossy cabinetry, stone benchtops and a breakfast bar. Flowing on from the kitchen is a study, the family dining area and main loungeroom.

All four bedrooms are generously sized with built-in robes, and are served by the large main bathroom. The spacious master bedroom offers a quiet space to retreat to at the end of a long day with plantation shutters, a view of the front garden, and an ensuite bathroom with a spa bath.
Enjoy a large workshop/storage space with split-system air conditioning, complemented by 3,000L Colourbond water tanks with electric pumps in both the front and back yards.

Located in a sought after area, the home is in close proximity to sporting fields, playgrounds, shops, schools, and restaurants, while Melbourne's CBD is just over half an hour away. Showcasing the perfect mix of style, location, and space, this will not last long!

The additional bedrooms and a dedicated laundry further enhance the practicality and luxury of the home. Moreover, the apartment includes a private home theater, allowing you to enjoy an immersive movie experience at home, which adds to the prestigious nature of the property. There is also a spacious outdoor entertaining area, perfect for hosting guests while savoring the magnificent views. Other highlights include a secure parking space and storage unit, with additional long-term parking available if needed. The Promenade project is ideally located in the vibrant Box Hill area, offering a variety of top-notch restaurants, grocery stores, and Asian convenience stores, along with childcare facilities and wellness spas, with convenient public transport access to the Central Business District and beyond (Express 18 mins).

Indoor area: approximately 247 square meters; outdoor area: approximately 193 square meters; builder: Hickory; architect: PEDDLE THORP Architecture; landscape design: John Patrick; developer: CBR Development Group. title: 999 BOX HILL HEART
description:
Effortless Living Meets Modern Brilliance

Exemplifying stress-free living, this deluxe apartment at 999 showcases modern brilliance at the gateway to Melbourne’s CBD. With easy access to the Eastern Freeway and just 15 minutes by express train from Richmond, Station Street is the ideal address for those seeking a contemporary, carefree lifestyle.

Design with Purpose and Tranquility

Each residence is crafted with thoughtful details that make everyday living seamless—from hidden laundry solutions to intelligently integrated kitchens and elegant bathrooms. A focus on both form and function results in a home that is as practical as it is beautiful.

The generously sized, sun-drenched balcony invites indoor-outdoor living, while private bedrooms—complete with built-in robes—are set apart from the communal areas for optimal privacy. The luxurious bathrooms are finished with high-quality materials, elevating daily rituals into moments of elegance.

A New Standard for Contemporary Living

999 redefines modern living in Melbourne, combining aesthetic refinement with purposeful design. It's not just a place to live—it’s a lifestyle crafted for those who appreciate the beauty of simplicity and the ease of thoughtful functionality.

description:

Positioned within walking distance of Athol Road Primary School and zoned for Keysborough Secondary College, this property offers excellent convenience for families. Springvale South Shopping Centre is located nearby, while Alex Wilke Nature Reserve and Alex Nelson Reserve are only a stone’s throw away. The 813 bus stop is within walking distance, and Noble Park Train Station is just minutes away by car.

The design is typical of Victoria’s mid-20th century suburbs. Its facade is defined by a symmetrical layout with a recessed central entry and picture windows that fill the living areas with natural light. Vertical timber cladding across the lower facade and simple rectangular proportions emphasise function, while the addition of rooftop solar panels brings efficiency.

The home feels bright and welcoming, with high ceilings and polished timber hardwood floors that emphasise space. Natural light filters easily through the open-plan layout, while the combination of a formal dining room and separate lounge offers flexibility. Comfort is catered for with classic pendant lighting, roller blinds, security screen doors, reverse cycle AC and a wall heater.

Outdoors, the property presents a large rolling backyard that offers plenty of space for children, entertaining or future updates. A covered pergola creates an inviting entertaining zone, framed by neat landscaping and supported by a secure front fence with vehicle and pedestrian access.

The kitchen showcases modern updates, with 40mm stone benchtops, a traditional tiled splash-back and soft close cabinetry that provides ample storage. Home chefs will appreciate the electric cooktop and oven, complemented by a gourmet range-hood, a contemporary mixer tap.

The home consists of three bedrooms, serviced by a central bathroom fitted with a stone-top vanity and a disabled access shower with vinyl flooring, handrail and glass screen. A separate guest powder room and a generous laundry enhance the home’s functionality.

Practical additions such as an external storage shed, a single carport and abundant off-street parking complete the appeal of this unique offering.

Contact us today to arrange a priority inspection.

title: Spacious Family Living with Privacy, Style & Prime Village Location
description:
This four-bedroom home provides exceptional security, privacy, and a prime location in the sought-after Dingley Village.
Enter through the roller-door carport or the secure front gate to discover a charming, north-facing verandah that sets the tone for effortless entertaining. Enjoy a glass-enclosed spa, a covered alfresco area, and ample space to relax, unwind, or entertain guests.
The home features beautiful wooden floors throughout and offers plenty of space. The spacious front lounge and dining area seamlessly flows into a well-equipped kitchen, featuring a dishwasher, gas cooktop, ample storage, and a cozy meals area. Additional features include a separate laundry, ducted gas heating, evaporative cooling, and solar-powered electricity.
There is also a spacious, light-filled living area with French doors opening onto the verandah for entertaining and casual meals.
The spacious master bedroom features a charming bay window and a generous walk-through ensuite that leads to a walk-in robe. Three additional bedrooms all include built-in robes, complemented by a central family bathroom. A separate study adds extra flexibility for work or relaxation.
Outside, you'll find a charming backyard featuring a delightful cubby house and a handy garden shed tucked around the corner.
Conveniently located close to schools and parks, this home is just moments from village shops and cafés. It's also a short drive to Kingston Plaza, Southland Shopping Centre, and the beautiful bay beaches.

Perfectly suited for everyday activities, occasional entertaining, and future growth, it presents an exceptional opportunity for families seeking spacious comfort, practicality, and value. Upon entry, discover open plan living and dining, an updated kitchen with ample storage and bench space, a separate water closet, and a large laundry with external access. Upstairs are three robed bedrooms and two renovated bathrooms, including a master with a walk-in robe, private ensuite, and balcony access. Comfortably serviced by under stair storage along with heating and cooling systems, the home also features a large backyard, garden shed, and double garage. Worthy of mention is the established lemon tree, providing plenty of citrus fruit for the household and neighbours!


Centrally located, this home is within walking distance of Noble Park shops and eateries, Noble Park Aquatic Centre, Ross Reserve, Noble Park Primary School, Noble Park Secondary College, and public transport including the train station and buses. It also enjoys proximity to Springvale Shopping Centre and Parkmore Shopping Centre.
